69bool IsInitializationOp(const Node* node) {
70 return node->op_def().allows_uninitialized_input();

73// Sets the timeline_label field of *node_stats, using data from *node.
74// Returns true iff the node is a transfer node.
75// TODO(tucker): merge with the DetailText function in session.cc
76// in a common location.
77bool SetTimelineLabel(const Node* node, NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
78 bool is_transfer_node = false;
79 if (!stats) {
80 return is_transfer_node;
81 }
82 string memory;
83 for (auto& all : stats->stats()->memory()) {
84 int64 tot = all.total_bytes();
85 if (tot >= 0.1 * 1048576.0) {
86 int64 peak = all.peak_bytes();
87 if (peak > 0) {
88 memory =
89 strings::StrCat(memory, "[", all.allocator_name(),
90 strings::Printf(" %.1fMB %.1fMB] ", tot / 1048576.0,
91 peak / 1048576.0));
92 } else {
93 memory = strings::StrCat(memory, "[", all.allocator_name(),
94 strings::Printf(" %.1fMB] ", tot / 1048576.0));
95 }
96 }
97 }
98 const AttrSlice attrs = node->attrs();
99 string text;
100 if (IsSend(node)) {
101 string tensor_name;
102 TF_CHECK_OK(GetNodeAttr(attrs, "tensor_name", &tensor_name));
103 string recv_device;
104 TF_CHECK_OK(GetNodeAttr(attrs, "recv_device", &recv_device));
105 text = strings::StrCat(memory, node->name(), " = ", node->type_string(),
106 "(", tensor_name, " @", recv_device);
107 is_transfer_node = true;
108 } else if (IsRecv(node)) {
109 string tensor_name;
110 TF_CHECK_OK(GetNodeAttr(attrs, "tensor_name", &tensor_name));
111 string send_device;
112 TF_CHECK_OK(GetNodeAttr(attrs, "send_device", &send_device));
113 text = strings::StrCat(memory, node->name(), " = ", node->type_string(),
114 "(", tensor_name, " @", send_device);
115 is_transfer_node = true;
116 } else {
117 text =
118 strings::StrCat(memory, node->name(), " = ", node->type_string(), "(",
119 str_util::Join(node->requested_inputs(), ", "), ")");
120 }
121 stats->stats()->set_timeline_label(text);
122 return is_transfer_node;
123}

125// Helper routines for collecting step stats.
126namespace nodestats {
127inline int64 NowInUsec() { return Env::Default()->NowMicros(); }
128
129void SetScheduled(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats, int64 t) {
130 if (!stats) return;
131 stats->stats()->set_scheduled_micros(t);
132}
133
134void SetAllStart(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
135 if (!stats) return;
136 stats->stats()->set_all_start_micros(NowInUsec());
137}
138
139void SetOpStart(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
140 if (!stats) return;
141 NodeExecStats* nt = stats->stats();
142 DCHECK_NE(nt->all_start_micros(), 0);
143 nt->set_op_start_rel_micros(NowInUsec() - nt->all_start_micros());
144}
145
146void SetOpEnd(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
147 if (!stats) return;
148 NodeExecStats* nt = stats->stats();
149 DCHECK_NE(nt->all_start_micros(), 0);
150 nt->set_op_end_rel_micros(NowInUsec() - nt->all_start_micros());
151}
152
153void SetAllEnd(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
154 if (!stats) return;
155 NodeExecStats* nt = stats->stats();
156 DCHECK_NE(nt->all_start_micros(), 0);
157 nt->set_all_end_rel_micros(NowInUsec() - nt->all_start_micros());
158}
159
160void SetOutput(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats, int slot, const Tensor* v) {
161 if (!stats) return;
162 DCHECK(v);
163 NodeOutput* no = stats->stats()->add_output();
164 no->set_slot(slot);
165 v->FillDescription(no->mutable_tensor_description());
166}
167
168void SetMemory(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats, OpKernelContext* ctx) {
169 if (!stats) return;
170
171 for (const auto& allocator_pair : ctx->wrapped_allocators()) {
172 stats->AddAllocation(allocator_pair.first, allocator_pair.second);
173 }
174 auto* ms = stats->stats()->mutable_memory_stats();
175 ms->set_temp_memory_size(ctx->temp_memory_allocated());
176 for (const auto& alloc_id : ctx->persistent_alloc_ids()) {
177 ms->mutable_persistent_tensor_alloc_ids()->Add(alloc_id);
178 }
179 ms->set_persistent_memory_size(ctx->persistent_memory_allocated());
180}
181
182void SetReferencedTensors(NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats,
183 const TensorReferenceVector& tensors) {
184 if (!stats) return;
185 // be careful not to increment the reference count on any tensor
186 // while recording the information
187 for (size_t i = 0; i < tensors.size(); ++i) {
188 AllocationDescription* description =
189 stats->stats()->add_referenced_tensor();
190 tensors.at(i).FillDescription(description);
191 }
192}

199struct EdgeInfo {
200 int dst_id;
201 int output_slot : 31;
202 // true if this is the last info for output_slot in the EdgeInfo list.
203 bool is_last : 1;
204 int input_slot;
205};
206
207struct NodeItem {
208 NodeItem() {}
209
210 // A graph node.
211 const Node* node = nullptr;
212
213 // The kernel for this node.
214 OpKernel* kernel = nullptr;
215
216 bool kernel_is_expensive : 1; // True iff kernel->IsExpensive()
217 bool kernel_is_async : 1; // True iff kernel->AsAsync() != nullptr
218 bool is_merge : 1; // True iff IsMerge(node)
219 bool is_enter : 1; // True iff IsEnter(node)
220 bool is_exit : 1; // True iff IsExit(node)
221 bool is_control_trigger : 1; // True iff IsControlTrigger(node)
222 bool is_sink : 1; // True iff IsSink(node)
223 // True iff IsEnter(node) || IsExit(node) || IsNextIteration(node)
224 bool is_enter_exit_or_next_iter : 1;
225
226 // Cached values of node->num_inputs() and node->num_outputs(), to
227 // avoid levels of indirection.
228 int num_inputs;
229 int num_outputs;
230
231 // ExecutorImpl::tensors_[input_start] is the 1st positional input
232 // for this node.
233 int input_start = 0;
234
235 // Number of output edges.
236 size_t num_output_edges;
237
238 PendingCounts::Handle pending_id;
239
240 const EdgeInfo* output_edge_list() const { return output_edge_base(); }
241
242 // ith output edge.
243 const EdgeInfo& output_edge(int i) const {
244 DCHECK_GE(i, 0);
245 DCHECK_LT(i, num_output_edges);
246 return output_edge_base()[i];
247 }
248
249 DataType input_type(int i) const {
250 DCHECK_LT(i, num_inputs);
251 return static_cast<DataType>(input_type_base()[i]);
252 }
253 DataType output_type(int i) const {
254 DCHECK_LT(i, num_outputs);
255 return static_cast<DataType>(output_type_base()[i]);
256 }
257
258 // Return array of per-output allocator attributes.
259 const AllocatorAttributes* output_attrs() const { return output_attr_base(); }
260
261 // Return array of expected input index from which each output should
262 // be forwarded:
263 // kNeverForward (-2) for DO NOT FORWARD (must allocate).
264 // kNoReservation (-1) for no expected forwarding.
265 // 0... for forward from that input.
266 const int* forward_from() const { return forward_from_base(); }
267
268 private:
269 friend class GraphView;
270
271 // Variable length section starts immediately after *this
272 // (uint8 is enough for DataType).
273 // EdgeInfo out_edges[num_out_edges];
274 // AllocatorAttributes output_attr[num_outputs];
275 // uint8 input_type[num_inputs];
276 // uint8 output_type[num_outputs];
277 // int forward_from[num_outputs];
278
279 // Return pointer to variable length section.
280 char* var() const {
281 return const_cast<char*>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(this) +
282 sizeof(NodeItem));
283 }
284
285 EdgeInfo* output_edge_base() const {
286 return reinterpret_cast<EdgeInfo*>(var());
287 }
288 AllocatorAttributes* output_attr_base() const {
289 return reinterpret_cast<AllocatorAttributes*>(var() + sizeof(EdgeInfo) *
290 num_output_edges);
291 }
292 uint8* input_type_base() const {
293 return reinterpret_cast<uint8*>(var() +
294 sizeof(EdgeInfo) * num_output_edges +
295 sizeof(AllocatorAttributes) * num_outputs);
296 }
297 uint8* output_type_base() const {
298 return reinterpret_cast<uint8*>(
299 var() + sizeof(EdgeInfo) * num_output_edges +
300 sizeof(AllocatorAttributes) * num_outputs + sizeof(uint8) * num_inputs);
301 }
302
303 int* forward_from_base() const {
304 return reinterpret_cast<int*>(var() + sizeof(EdgeInfo) * num_output_edges +
305 sizeof(AllocatorAttributes) * num_outputs +
306 sizeof(uint8) * num_inputs +
307 sizeof(uint8) * num_outputs);
308 }
309
310 TF_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(NodeItem);
311};
312
313typedef gtl::InlinedVector<TensorValue, 4> TensorValueVec;
314typedef gtl::InlinedVector<DeviceContext*, 4> DeviceContextVec;
315typedef gtl::InlinedVector<AllocatorAttributes, 4> AllocatorAttributeVec;
316
317// Immutable view of a Graph organized for efficient execution.
318class GraphView {
319 public:
320 GraphView() : space_(nullptr) {}
321 ~GraphView();
322
323 void Initialize(const Graph* g);
324 Status SetAllocAttrs(const Graph* g, const Device* device);
325
326 NodeItem* node(size_t id) const {
327 DCHECK_GE(id, 0);
328 DCHECK_LT(id, num_nodes_);
329 uint32 offset = node_offsets_[id];
330 return ((offset == kuint32max)
331 ? nullptr
332 : reinterpret_cast<NodeItem*>(space_ + node_offsets_[id]));
333 }
334
335 private:
336 char* InitializeNode(char* ptr, const Node* n);
337 size_t NodeItemBytes(const Node* n);
338
339 int32 num_nodes_ = 0;
340 uint32* node_offsets_ = nullptr; // array of size "graph_.num_node_ids()"
341 // node_offsets_[id] holds the byte offset for node w/ "id" in space_
342
343 char* space_; // NodeItem objects are allocated here
344
345 TF_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(GraphView);
346};

348class ExecutorImpl : public Executor {
349 public:
350 ExecutorImpl(const LocalExecutorParams& p, std::unique_ptr<const Graph> g)
351 : params_(p), graph_(std::move(g)), gview_() {
352 CHECK(p.create_kernel != nullptr);
353 CHECK(p.delete_kernel != nullptr);
354 }
355
356 ~ExecutorImpl() override {
357 for (int i = 0; i < graph_->num_node_ids(); i++) {
358 NodeItem* item = gview_.node(i);
359 if (item != nullptr) {
360 params_.delete_kernel(item->kernel);
361 }
362 }
363 for (auto fiter : frame_info_) {
364 delete fiter.second;
365 }
366 }

368 Status Initialize();

370 // Process all Nodes in the current graph, attempting to infer the
371 // memory allocation attributes to be used wherever they may allocate
372 // a tensor buffer.
373 Status SetAllocAttrs();
374
375 void RunAsync(const Args& args, DoneCallback done) override;
376
377 private:
378 friend class ExecutorState;

380 struct ControlFlowInfo {
381 gtl::FlatSet<string> unique_frame_names;
382 std::vector<string> frame_names;
383 };
384
385 struct FrameInfo {
386 FrameInfo()
387 : input_count(0),
388 total_inputs(0),
389 pending_counts(nullptr),
390 nodes(nullptr) {}
391
392 // The total number of inputs to a frame.
393 int input_count;
394
395 // The total number of input tensors of a frame.
396 // == sum(nodes[*].num_inputs()) where nodes are the nodes in the frame.
397 int total_inputs;
398
399 // Used to determine the next place to allocate space in the
400 // pending_counts data structure we'll eventually construct
401 PendingCounts::Layout pending_counts_layout;
402
403 // Each frame has its own PendingCounts only for the nodes in the frame.
404 PendingCounts* pending_counts; // Owned
405
406 // The nodes in a frame. Used only for debugging.
407 std::vector<const Node*>* nodes; // Owned
408
409 ~FrameInfo() {
410 delete pending_counts;
411 delete nodes;
412 }
413 };
414
415 static Status BuildControlFlowInfo(const Graph* graph,
416 ControlFlowInfo* cf_info);
417 void InitializePending(const Graph* graph, const ControlFlowInfo& cf_info);
418
419 FrameInfo* EnsureFrameInfo(const string& fname) {
420 auto slot = &frame_info_[fname];
421 if (*slot == nullptr) {
422 *slot = new FrameInfo;
423 }
424 return *slot;
425 }
426
427 // Owned.
428 LocalExecutorParams params_;
429 std::unique_ptr<const Graph> graph_;
430 GraphView gview_;
431
432 // A cached value of params_
433 bool device_record_tensor_accesses_ = false;
434
435 // Root nodes (with no in edges) that should form the initial ready queue
436 std::vector<const Node*> root_nodes_;
437
438 // Mapping from frame name to static information about the frame.
439 // TODO(yuanbyu): We could cache it along with the graph so to avoid
440 // the overhead of constructing it for each executor instance.
441 gtl::FlatMap<string, FrameInfo*> frame_info_;
442
443 TF_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(ExecutorImpl);
444};

446// Infer memory allocation attributes of a node n's output,
447// based on its use node dst. Note that dst might not be directly
448// connected to n by a single edge, but might be a downstream
449// consumer of n's output by reference. *attr is updated with any
450// necessary attributes.
451Status InferAllocAttr(const Node* n, const Node* dst,
452 const DeviceNameUtils::ParsedName& local_dev_name,
453 AllocatorAttributes* attr);
454
455GraphView::~GraphView() {
456 static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible<AllocatorAttributes>::value,
457 "Update code if AllocatorAttributes gains a destructor");
458 static_assert(std::is_trivially_destructible<EdgeInfo>::value,
459 "Update code if EdgeInfo gains a destructor");
460 for (int i = 0; i < num_nodes_; i++) {
461 NodeItem* n = node(i);
462 if (n != nullptr) {
463 n->NodeItem::~NodeItem();
464 // Memory for "n" itself is held in space_ & gets cleaned up below
465 }
466 }
467 delete[] node_offsets_;
468 delete[] space_;
469}
470
471size_t GraphView::NodeItemBytes(const Node* n) {
472 const size_t num_output_edges = n->out_edges().size();
473 const int num_inputs = n->num_inputs();
474 const int num_outputs = n->num_outputs();
475
476 // Compute number of bytes needed for NodeItem and variable length data.
477 // We do not subtract sizeof(var) since num_inputs/num_outputs might
478 // both be zero.
479 const size_t raw_bytes =
480 sizeof(NodeItem) // Fixed
481 + num_output_edges * sizeof(EdgeInfo) // output_edges[...]
482 + num_outputs * sizeof(AllocatorAttributes) // output_attr[...]
483 + num_inputs * sizeof(uint8) // input_type[num_inputs]
484 + num_outputs * sizeof(uint8) // output_type[num_outputs]
485 + num_outputs * sizeof(int); // forward_from[num_outputs]
486 static constexpr size_t kItemAlignment = sizeof(NodeItem*);
487 static_assert(kItemAlignment % alignof(NodeItem) == 0,
488 "NodeItem must be aligned with kItemAlignment");
489 static_assert(kItemAlignment % alignof(EdgeInfo) == 0,
490 "EdgeInfo must be aligned with kItemAlignment");
491 static_assert(kItemAlignment % alignof(AllocatorAttributes) == 0,
492 "AllocatorAttributes must be aligned with kItemAlignment");
493 static_assert(sizeof(NodeItem) % alignof(EdgeInfo) == 0,
494 "NodeItem must be aligned with EdgeInfo");
495 static_assert(sizeof(NodeItem) % alignof(AllocatorAttributes) == 0,
496 "NodeItem must be aligned with AllocatorAttributes");
497 static_assert(sizeof(EdgeInfo) % alignof(AllocatorAttributes) == 0,
498 "EdgeInfo must be aligned with AllocatorAttributes");
499 const size_t bytes =
500 ((raw_bytes + kItemAlignment - 1) / kItemAlignment) * kItemAlignment;
501 return bytes;
502}
503
504char* GraphView::InitializeNode(char* ptr, const Node* n) {
505 const int id = n->id();
506 CHECK(node_offsets_[id] == kuint32max); // Initial value in constructor
507
508 const size_t bytes = NodeItemBytes(n);
509 constexpr size_t kItemAlignment = sizeof(NodeItem*);
510 CHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(ptr) % kItemAlignment, 0);
511 NodeItem* item = reinterpret_cast<NodeItem*>(ptr);
512
513 // We store a 32-bit offset relative to the beginning of space_, so that we
514 // only need an array of 32-bit values to map from node id to the NodeItem*,
515 // (versus 64 bits on most machines if we just stored an array of NodeItem*
516 // pointers). Casting to int64 is needed on 32bit CPU to avoid comparing
517 // values as "int" vs "size_t" in CHECK_LE.
518 CHECK_LE(static_cast<int64>(ptr - space_), kuint32max);
519 const uint32 offset = static_cast<uint32>(ptr - space_);
520 node_offsets_[id] = offset;
521 ptr += bytes;
522
523 const size_t num_output_edges = n->out_edges().size();
524 const int num_inputs = n->num_inputs();
525 const int num_outputs = n->num_outputs();
526
527 new (item) NodeItem();
528 item->num_inputs = num_inputs;
529 item->num_outputs = num_outputs;
530 item->num_output_edges = num_output_edges;
531
532 // Fill output edges.
533 // Keep track of the last EdgeInfo in the EdgeInfo array that references
534 // a given output slot. For all but the last, we need to do a copy of the
535 // Tensor when propagating results downstream in the graph, but for the
536 // last one, we can just do a move of the Tensor object to propagate it.
537 gtl::InlinedVector<EdgeInfo*, 4> last_indices(num_outputs, nullptr);
538 EdgeInfo* dst_edge = item->output_edge_base();
539 for (auto e : n->out_edges()) {
540 dst_edge->dst_id = e->dst()->id();
541 CHECK_LE(e->src_output(), 0x3FFFFFFF); // Must fit in 31 bits
542 dst_edge->output_slot = e->src_output();
543 dst_edge->is_last = false;
544 const int output_slot = dst_edge->output_slot;
545 if (output_slot >= 0) {
546 last_indices[output_slot] = dst_edge;
547 }
548 dst_edge->input_slot = e->dst_input();
549 dst_edge++;
550 }
551 for (EdgeInfo* edge_info : last_indices) {
552 if (edge_info != nullptr) {
553 edge_info->is_last = true;
554 }
555 }
556
557 AllocatorAttributes* output_attrs = item->output_attr_base();
558 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; i++) {
559 new (&output_attrs[i]) AllocatorAttributes();
560 }
561
562 DCHECK_LT(DataType_MAX, 255); // Must fit in uint8
563 uint8* input_types = item->input_type_base();
564 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; i++) {
565 input_types[i] = static_cast<uint8>(n->input_type(i));
566 DCHECK_EQ(item->input_type(i), n->input_type(i));
567 }
568
569 uint8* output_types = item->output_type_base();
570 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; i++) {
571 output_types[i] = static_cast<uint8>(n->output_type(i));
572 DCHECK_EQ(item->output_type(i), n->output_type(i));
573 }
574 return ptr;
575}
576
577void GraphView::Initialize(const Graph* g) {
578 CHECK(node_offsets_ == nullptr);
579 const int num_nodes = g->num_node_ids();
580 num_nodes_ = num_nodes;
581 size_t total_bytes = 0;
582 for (const Node* n : g->nodes()) {
583 total_bytes += NodeItemBytes(n);
584 }
585
586 node_offsets_ = new uint32[num_nodes];
587 for (int i = 0; i < num_nodes; i++) {
588 node_offsets_[i] = kuint32max;
589 }
590
591 space_ = new char[total_bytes]; // NodeItem objects are allocated here
592 char* ptr = space_;
593 for (const Node* n : g->nodes()) {
594 ptr = InitializeNode(ptr, n);
595 }
596 CHECK_EQ(ptr, space_ + total_bytes);
597}
598
599void GetMaxPendingCounts(const Node* n, size_t* max_pending,
600 size_t* max_dead_count) {
601 const size_t num_in_edges = n->in_edges().size();
602 size_t initial_count;
603 if (IsMerge(n)) {
604 // merge waits all control inputs so we initialize the pending
605 // count to be the number of control edges.
606 int32 num_control_edges = 0;
607 for (const Edge* edge : n->in_edges()) {
608 if (edge->IsControlEdge()) {
609 num_control_edges++;
610 }
611 }
612 // Use bit 0 to indicate if we are waiting for a ready live data input.
613 initial_count = 1 + (num_control_edges << 1);
614 } else {
615 initial_count = num_in_edges;
616 }
617
618 *max_pending = initial_count;
619 *max_dead_count = num_in_edges;
620}
621
622Status ExecutorImpl::Initialize() {
623 gview_.Initialize(graph_.get());
624
625 // Build the information about frames in this subgraph.
626 ControlFlowInfo cf_info;
627 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(BuildControlFlowInfo(graph_.get(), &cf_info));
628
629 // Cache this value so we make this virtual function call once, rather
630 // that O(# steps * # nodes per step) times.
631 device_record_tensor_accesses_ =
632 params_.device->RequiresRecordingAccessedTensors();
633
634 for (auto& it : cf_info.unique_frame_names) {
635 EnsureFrameInfo(it)->nodes = new std::vector<const Node*>;
636 }
637
638 // Preprocess every node in the graph to create an instance of op
639 // kernel for each node.
640 for (const Node* n : graph_->nodes()) {
641 const int id = n->id();
642 const string& frame_name = cf_info.frame_names[id];
643 FrameInfo* frame_info = EnsureFrameInfo(frame_name);
644
645 // See if this node is a root node, and if so, add to root_nodes_.
646 if (n->in_edges().empty()) {
647 root_nodes_.push_back(n);
648 }
649
650 NodeItem* item = gview_.node(id);
651 item->node = n;
652
653 item->input_start = frame_info->total_inputs;
654 frame_info->total_inputs += n->num_inputs();
655
656 Status s = params_.create_kernel(n->def(), &item->kernel);
657 if (!s.ok()) {
658 item->kernel = nullptr;
659 s = AttachDef(s, *n);
660 LOG(ERROR) << "Executor failed to create kernel. " << s;
661 return s;
662 }
663 CHECK(item->kernel);
664 item->kernel_is_expensive = item->kernel->IsExpensive();
665 item->kernel_is_async = (item->kernel->AsAsync() != nullptr);
666 item->is_merge = IsMerge(n);
667 item->is_enter = IsEnter(n);
668 item->is_exit = IsExit(n);
669 item->is_control_trigger = IsControlTrigger(n);
670 item->is_sink = IsSink(n);
671 item->is_enter_exit_or_next_iter =
672 (IsEnter(n) || IsExit(n) || IsNextIteration(n));
673
674 // Compute the maximum values we'll store for this node in the
675 // pending counts data structure, and allocate a handle in
676 // that frame's pending counts data structure that has enough
677 // space to store these maximal count values.
678 size_t max_pending, max_dead;
679 GetMaxPendingCounts(n, &max_pending, &max_dead);
680 item->pending_id =
681 frame_info->pending_counts_layout.CreateHandle(max_pending, max_dead);
682
683 // Initialize static information about the frames in the graph.
684 frame_info->nodes->push_back(n);
685 if (IsEnter(n)) {
686 string enter_name;
687 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(GetNodeAttr(n->attrs(), "frame_name", &enter_name));
688 EnsureFrameInfo(enter_name)->input_count++;
689 }
690 }
691
692 // Initialize PendingCounts only after item->pending_id is initialized for
693 // all nodes.
694 InitializePending(graph_.get(), cf_info);
695
696 return gview_.SetAllocAttrs(graph_.get(), params_.device);
697}
698
699Status GraphView::SetAllocAttrs(const Graph* g, const Device* device) {
700 Status s;
701 DeviceNameUtils::ParsedName local_dev_name = device->parsed_name();
702
703 for (const Node* n : g->nodes()) {
704 NodeItem* item = node(n->id());
705 AllocatorAttributes* attrs = item->output_attr_base();
706
707 // Examine the out edges of each node looking for special use
708 // cases that may affect memory allocation attributes.
709 for (auto e : n->out_edges()) {
710 if (!e->IsControlEdge()) {
711 AllocatorAttributes attr;
712 s = InferAllocAttr(n, e->dst(), local_dev_name, &attr);
713 if (!s.ok()) return s;
714 if (attr.value != 0) {
715 attrs[e->src_output()].Merge(attr);
716 }
717 }
718 }
719
720 for (int out = 0; out < n->num_outputs(); out++) {
721 const OpKernel* op_kernel = item->kernel;
722 DCHECK_LT(out, op_kernel->output_memory_types().size());
723 bool on_host = op_kernel->output_memory_types()[out] == HOST_MEMORY;
724 if (on_host) {
725 AllocatorAttributes h;
726 h.set_on_host(on_host);
727 attrs[out].Merge(h);
728 }
729 }
730 }
731 return s;
732}
733
734Status InferAllocAttr(const Node* n, const Node* dst,
735 const DeviceNameUtils::ParsedName& local_dev_name,
736 AllocatorAttributes* attr) {
737 Status s;
738 // Note that it's possible for *n to be a Recv and *dst to be a Send,
739 // so these two cases are not mutually exclusive.
740 if (IsRecv(n)) {
741 string src_name;
742 s = GetNodeAttr(n->attrs(), "send_device", &src_name);
743 if (!s.ok()) return s;
744 DeviceNameUtils::ParsedName parsed_src_name;
745 if (!DeviceNameUtils::ParseFullName(src_name, &parsed_src_name)) {
746 s = errors::Internal("Bad send_device attr '", src_name, "' in node ",
747 n->name());
748 return s;
749 }
750 if (!DeviceNameUtils::IsSameAddressSpace(parsed_src_name, local_dev_name)) {
751 // Value is going to be the sink of an RPC.
752 attr->set_nic_compatible(true);
753 VLOG(2) << "node " << n->name() << " is the sink of an RPC in";
754 } else if ((local_dev_name.type == "CPU" || n->IsHostRecv()) &&
755 parsed_src_name.type != "CPU") {
756 // Value is going to be the sink of a local DMA from GPU to CPU (or
757 // other types of accelerators).
758 attr->set_gpu_compatible(true);
759 VLOG(2) << "node " << n->name() << " is the sink of a gpu->cpu copy";
760 } else {
761 VLOG(2) << "default alloc case local type " << local_dev_name.type
762 << " remote type " << parsed_src_name.type;
763 }
764 }
765 if (IsSend(dst)) {
766 string dst_name;
767 s = GetNodeAttr(dst->attrs(), "recv_device", &dst_name);
768 if (!s.ok()) return s;
769 DeviceNameUtils::ParsedName parsed_dst_name;
770 if (!DeviceNameUtils::ParseFullName(dst_name, &parsed_dst_name)) {
771 s = errors::Internal("Bad recv_device attr '", dst_name, "' in node ",
772 n->name());
773 return s;
774 }
775 if (!DeviceNameUtils::IsSameAddressSpace(parsed_dst_name, local_dev_name)) {
776 // Value is going to be the source of an RPC.
777 attr->set_nic_compatible(true);
778 VLOG(2) << "node " << n->name() << " is the source of an RPC out";
779 } else if ((local_dev_name.type == "CPU" || dst->IsHostSend()) &&
780 parsed_dst_name.type != "CPU") {
781 // Value is going to be the source of a local DMA from CPU to GPU (or
782 // other types of accelerators).
783 // Note that this does not cover the case where the allocation of the
784 // output tensor is not generated by the src: n.
785 attr->set_gpu_compatible(true);
786 VLOG(2) << "node " << n->name() << " is the source of a cpu->gpu copy";
787 } else {
788 VLOG(2) << "default alloc case local type " << local_dev_name.type
789 << " remote type " << parsed_dst_name.type;
790 }
791 }
792 return s;
793}
794
795// The state associated with one invocation of ExecutorImpl::Run.
796// ExecutorState dispatches nodes when they become ready and keeps
797// track of how many predecessors of a node have not done (pending_).
798class ExecutorState {
799 public:
800 ExecutorState(const Executor::Args& args, ExecutorImpl* impl);
801 ~ExecutorState();
802
803 void RunAsync(Executor::DoneCallback done);
804
805 private:
806 // Either a tensor pointer (pass-by-reference) or a tensor (pass-by-value).
807 // TODO(yuanbyu): A better way to do "has_value"?
808 struct Entry {
809 Entry() {}
810 Entry(const Entry& other)
811 : ref(other.ref),
812 ref_mu(other.ref_mu),
813 has_value(other.has_value),
814 val_field_is_set(other.val_field_is_set),
815 alloc_attr(other.alloc_attr),
816 device_context(other.device_context) {
817 if (val_field_is_set) {
818 val.Init(*other.val);
819 }
820 }
821 ~Entry() {
822 if (val_field_is_set) val.Destroy();
823 }
824
825 Entry& operator=(const Entry& other) {
826 if (val_field_is_set) {
827 val.Destroy();
828 }
829 ref = other.ref;
830 ref_mu = other.ref_mu;
831 has_value = other.has_value;
832 val_field_is_set = other.val_field_is_set;
833 alloc_attr = other.alloc_attr;
834 device_context = other.device_context;
835 if (val_field_is_set) {
836 val.Init(*other.val);
837 }
838 return *this;
839 }
840
841 Entry& operator=(Entry&& other) {
842 if (val_field_is_set) {
843 val.Destroy();
844 }
845 ref = other.ref;
846 ref_mu = other.ref_mu;
847 has_value = other.has_value;
848 val_field_is_set = other.val_field_is_set;
849 alloc_attr = other.alloc_attr;
850 device_context = other.device_context;
851 if (val_field_is_set) {
852 val.Init(std::move(*other.val));
853 }
854 return *this;
855 }
856
857 // Clears the <val> field.
858 void ClearVal() {
859 if (val_field_is_set) {
860 val.Destroy();
861 val_field_is_set = false;
862 has_value = false;
863 }
864 }
865
866 // A tensor value, if val_field_is_set.
867 ManualConstructor<Tensor> val;
868
869 Tensor* ref = nullptr; // A tensor reference.
870 mutex* ref_mu = nullptr; // mutex for *ref if ref is not nullptr.
871
872 // Whether the value exists, either in <val> or <ref>.
873 bool has_value = false;
874
875 bool val_field_is_set = false;
876
877 // The attributes of the allocator that creates the tensor.
878 AllocatorAttributes alloc_attr;
879
880 // Every entry carries an optional DeviceContext containing
881 // Device-specific information about how the Tensor was produced.
882 DeviceContext* device_context = nullptr;
883 };
884
885 // Contains a value for [node->id()] for the device context assigned by the
886 // device at the beginning of a step.
887 DeviceContextMap device_context_map_;

889 struct TaggedNode;
890 typedef gtl::InlinedVector<TaggedNode, 8> TaggedNodeSeq;
891 typedef gtl::InlinedVector<Entry, 4> EntryVector;

893 struct IterationState {
894 explicit IterationState(const PendingCounts* pending_counts,
895 int total_input_tensors)
896 : input_tensors(new Entry[total_input_tensors]),
897 outstanding_ops(0),
898 outstanding_frame_count(0),
899 counts_(*pending_counts) { // Initialize with copy of *pending_counts
900 }
901
902 // The state of an iteration.
903
904 // One copy per iteration. For iteration k, i-th node's j-th input is in
905 // input_tensors[k][impl_->nodes[i].input_start + j]. An entry is either
906 // a tensor pointer (pass-by-reference) or a tensor (pass-by-value).
907 //
908 // NOTE: No need to protect input_tensors[i] by any locks because it
909 // is resized once. Each element of tensors_ is written once by the
910 // source node of an edge and is cleared by the destination of the same
911 // edge. The latter node is never run concurrently with the former node.
912 Entry* input_tensors;
913
914 // The number of outstanding ops for each iteration.
915 size_t outstanding_ops;
916
917 // The number of outstanding frames for each iteration.
918 int outstanding_frame_count;
919 int pending(PendingCounts::Handle h) { return counts_.pending(h); }
920 int decrement_pending(PendingCounts::Handle h, int v) {
921 return counts_.decrement_pending(h, v);
922 }
923 // Mark a merge node as live
924 // REQUIRES: Node corresponding to "h" is a merge node
925 void mark_live(PendingCounts::Handle h) { counts_.mark_live(h); }
926 // Mark a node to show that processing has started.
927 void mark_started(PendingCounts::Handle h) { counts_.mark_started(h); }
928 // Mark a node to show that processing has completed.
929 void mark_completed(PendingCounts::Handle h) { counts_.mark_completed(h); }
930 PendingCounts::NodeState node_state(PendingCounts::Handle h) {
931 return counts_.node_state(h);
932 }
933
934 int dead_count(PendingCounts::Handle h) { return counts_.dead_count(h); }
935 void increment_dead_count(PendingCounts::Handle h) {
936 counts_.increment_dead_count(h);
937 }
938 void adjust_for_activation(PendingCounts::Handle h, bool increment_dead,
939 int* pending_result, int* dead_result) {
940 counts_.adjust_for_activation(h, increment_dead, pending_result,
941 dead_result);
942 }
943
944 ~IterationState() { delete[] input_tensors; }
945
946 private:
947 PendingCounts counts_;
948 };
949
950 struct FrameState {
951 explicit FrameState(const ExecutorImpl* impl, int parallel_iters)
952 : executor(impl),
953 max_parallel_iterations(parallel_iters),
954 num_outstanding_iterations(1) {}
955
956 // A new frame is created for each loop. Execution starts at iteration 0.
957 // When a value at iteration 0 passes through a NextIteration node,
958 // iteration 1 is created and starts running. Note that iteration 0 may
959 // still be running so multiple iterations may run in parallel. The
960 // frame maintains the state of iterations in several data structures
961 // such as pending_count and input_tensors. When iteration 0 completes,
962 // we garbage collect the state of iteration 0.
963 //
964 // A frame instance is considered "done" and can be garbage collected
965 // if all its inputs have entered and all its iterations are "done".
966 //
967 // A frame manages the live iterations of an iterative computation.
968 // Iteration i is considered "done" when there are no outstanding ops,
969 // frames at iteration i are done, all recvs for this iteration are
970 // completed, and iteration i-1 is done. For iteration 0, we instead
971 // wait for there to be no more pending inputs of the frame.
972 //
973 // Frames and iterations are garbage collected once they are done.
974 // The state we need to keep around is highly dependent on the
975 // parallelism enabled by the scheduler. We may want to have the
976 // scheduler dynamically control the outstanding number of live
977 // parallel frames and iterations. To reduce the state space, the
978 // scheduler might want to schedule ops in inner frames first and
979 // lower iterations first.
980 //
981 // This frame state is mostly initialized lazily on demand so we
982 // don't introduce unnecessary overhead.
983
984 // The executor the frame is in.
985 const ExecutorImpl* executor = nullptr;
986
987 // The name of this frame, which is the concatenation of its parent
988 // frame name, the iteration of the parent frame when this frame was
989 // created, and the value of the attr 'frame_name'.
990 string frame_name;
991
992 // The unique id for this frame. Generated by fingerprinting
993 // frame_name.
994 uint64 frame_id;
995
996 // The iteration id of its parent frame when this frame is created.
997 // -1 if there is no parent frame. The frame_name/parent_iter pair
998 // uniquely identifies this FrameState.
999 int64 parent_iter = -1;
1000
1001 // The FrameState of its parent frame.
1002 FrameState* parent_frame = nullptr;
1003
1004 // The maximum allowed number of parallel iterations.
1005 const int max_parallel_iterations;
1006
1007 // The number of inputs this frame is still waiting.
1008 int num_pending_inputs = 0;
1009
1010 // The highest iteration number we have reached so far in this frame.
1011 int64 iteration_count GUARDED_BY(mu) = 0;
1012
1013 // The number of outstanding iterations.
1014 int num_outstanding_iterations GUARDED_BY(mu) = 1;
1015
1016 // The active iteration states of this frame.
1017 gtl::InlinedVector<IterationState*, 12> iterations;
1018
1019 // The NextIteration nodes to enter a new iteration. If the number of
1020 // outstanding iterations reaches the limit, we will defer the start of
1021 // the next iteration until the number of outstanding iterations falls
1022 // below the limit.
1023 std::vector<std::pair<const Node*, Entry>> next_iter_roots GUARDED_BY(mu);
1024
1025 // The values of the loop invariants for this loop. They are added into
1026 // this list as they "enter" the frame. When a loop invariant enters,
1027 // we make it available to all active iterations. When the frame starts
1028 // a new iteration, we make all the current loop invariants available
1029 // to the new iteration.
1030 std::vector<std::pair<const Node*, Entry>> inv_values GUARDED_BY(mu);
1031
1032 // The list of dead exit nodes for the current highest iteration. We
1033 // will only "execute" the dead exits of the final iteration.
1034 std::vector<const Node*> dead_exits GUARDED_BY(mu);
1035
1036 // Static information specific to this frame.
1037 PendingCounts* pending_counts = nullptr;
1038 int total_input_tensors = 0;
1039 std::vector<const Node*>* nodes = nullptr;
1040
1041 // Lock ordering: ExecutorState.mu_ < mu;
1042 // during structured traversal: parent_frame->mu < mu.
1043 mutex mu;
1044
1045 void InitializeFrameInfo(const string& enter_name) {
1046 auto it_frame_info = executor->frame_info_.find(enter_name);
1047 DCHECK(it_frame_info != executor->frame_info_.end());
1048 ExecutorImpl::FrameInfo* finfo = it_frame_info->second;
1049 pending_counts = finfo->pending_counts;
1050 total_input_tensors = finfo->total_inputs;
1051 num_pending_inputs = finfo->input_count;
1052 nodes = finfo->nodes;
1053 }
1054
1055 inline IterationState* GetIteration(int64 iter)
1056 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu) {
1057 size_t index = iter % iterations.size();
1058 return iterations[index];
1059 }
1060
1061 inline void SetIteration(int64 iter, IterationState* state)
1062 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu) {
1063 size_t index = iter % iterations.size();
1064 DCHECK(state == nullptr || iterations[index] == nullptr);
1065 iterations[index] = state;
1066 }
1067
1068 // Decrement the outstanding op count and clean up the iterations in the
1069 // frame. Return true iff the execution of the frame is done.
1070 inline bool DecrementOutstandingOps(const GraphView* gview, int64 iter,
1071 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
1072 mutex_lock l(mu);
1073 return DecrementOutstandingOpsLocked(gview, iter, ready);
1074 }
1075
1076 // Decrement the outstanding op count and clean up the iterations in the
1077 // frame. Return true iff the execution of the frame is done.
1078 inline bool DecrementOutstandingOpsLocked(const GraphView* gview,
1079 int64 iter, TaggedNodeSeq* ready)
1080 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu) {
1081 IterationState* istate = GetIteration(iter);
1082 istate->outstanding_ops--;
1083 if (istate->outstanding_ops != 0) {
1084 return false;
1085 } else {
1086 return CleanupIterations(gview, iter, ready);
1087 }
1088 }
1089
1090 // Returns true if the computation in the frame is completed.
1091 inline bool IsFrameDone() EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu) {
1092 return (num_pending_inputs == 0 && num_outstanding_iterations == 0);
1093 }
1094
1095 // Returns true if the iteration of the frame is completed.
1096 bool IsIterationDone(int64 iter) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1097
1098 // Increments the iteration id. If this is a new iteration, initialize it.
1099 void IncrementIteration(const GraphView* gview, TaggedNodeSeq* ready)
1100 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1101
1102 // Activate all the deferred NextIteration nodes in a new iteration.
1103 void ActivateNexts(const GraphView* gview, int64 iter, TaggedNodeSeq* ready)
1104 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1105
1106 // Activate all the current loop invariants in a new iteration.
1107 void ActivateLoopInvs(const GraphView* gview, int64 iter,
1108 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1109
1110 // Add a new loop invariant and make it available to all active
1111 // iterations.
1112 void AddLoopInv(const NodeItem* item, const Entry& value,
1113 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1114
1115 // Activate the successors of a node. Contents of *outputs are left in an
1116 // indeterminate state after returning from this method.
1117 void ActivateNodes(const NodeItem* item, const bool is_dead, int64 iter,
1118 EntryVector* outputs, TaggedNodeSeq* ready)
1119 EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1120
1121 // Cleanup iterations of this frame starting from iteration iter.
1122 bool CleanupIterations(const GraphView* gview, int64 iter,
1123 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mu);
1124
1125 ~FrameState() {
1126 for (size_t i = 0; i < iterations.size(); ++i) {
1127 delete iterations[i];
1128 iterations[i] = nullptr;
1129 }
1130 }
1131 };

1133 // A tagged node: <frame*, iter, node*>.
1134 struct TaggedNode {
1135 const Node* node = nullptr;
1136 FrameState* input_frame = nullptr;
1137 int64 input_iter = -1;
1138 bool is_dead = false;
1139
1140 TaggedNode(const Node* t_node, FrameState* in_frame, int64 in_iter,
1141 bool dead) {
1142 node = t_node;
1143 input_frame = in_frame;
1144 input_iter = in_iter;
1145 is_dead = dead;
1146 }
1147 };
1148
1149 // A drop-in replacement for std::deque<TaggedNode>. We typically don't
1150 // have that many nodes in the ready queue, so we just use a vector and
1151 // don't free up memory from the queue as we consume nodes.
1152 class TaggedNodeReadyQueue {
1153 public:
1154 TaggedNodeReadyQueue() : front_index_(0) {}
1155
1156 void push_back(TaggedNode node) { ready_.push_back(node); }
1157 TaggedNode front() const {
1158 DCHECK_LT(front_index_, ready_.size());
1159 return ready_[front_index_];
1160 }
1161 void pop_front() {
1162 DCHECK_LT(front_index_, ready_.size());
1163 front_index_++;
1164 if ((front_index_ == ready_.size()) || (front_index_ > 16384)) {
1165 if (front_index_ == ready_.size()) {
1166 ready_.clear();
1167 } else {
1168 // Lots of unused entries at beginning of vector: move everything
1169 // down to start of vector.
1170 ready_.erase(ready_.begin(), ready_.begin() + front_index_);
1171 }
1172 front_index_ = 0;
1173 }
1174 }
1175 bool empty() const { return ready_.empty(); }
1176 const TaggedNode* begin() const { return ready_.begin() + front_index_; }
1177 const TaggedNode* end() const { return ready_.end(); }
1178
1179 private:
1180 gtl::InlinedVector<TaggedNode, 16> ready_;
1181 int front_index_;
1182 };

1284
1285 // Provide debugging output about an outstanding node in the executor.
1286 void DumpPendingNodeState(const int node_id, const Entry* input_vector,
1287 bool show_nodes_with_no_ready_inputs);
1288 void DumpActiveNodeState(const int node_id, const Entry* input_vector);
1289
1290 // Provide debugging output about an outstanding iteration in the executor.
1291 void DumpIterationState(const FrameState* frame, IterationState* iteration);
1292
1293 // Provide debugging output of the state of the executor.
1294 void DumpState();
1295 const Tensor* GetTensorValueForDump(const Entry& input);
1296
1297 // Clean up when this executor is done.
1298 void Finish();
1299
1300 // A standalone routine for this expression so that we can express
1301 // that we don't want thread safety analysis on this reference (it's
1302 // safe to do without the lock because the iterations array never
1303 // resizes and this particular iteration's array element will not
1304 // be changed out from under us because the iteration is still alive).
1305 Entry* GetInputTensors(FrameState* input_frame,
1306 int64 input_iter) const NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
1307 return input_frame->GetIteration(input_iter)->input_tensors;
1308 }
1309};
1310
1311ExecutorState::ExecutorState(const Executor::Args& args, ExecutorImpl* impl)
1312 : vlog_(VLOG_IS_ON(1)),
1313 log_memory_(LogMemory::IsEnabled()),
1314 step_id_(args.step_id),
1315 rendezvous_(args.rendezvous),
1316 session_state_(args.session_state),
1317 tensor_store_(args.tensor_store),
1318 step_container_(args.step_container),
1319 stats_collector_(args.stats_collector),
1320 slice_reader_cache_(new checkpoint::TensorSliceReaderCacheWrapper),
1321 call_frame_(args.call_frame),
1322 impl_(impl),
1323 cancellation_manager_(args.cancellation_manager),
1324 runner_(args.runner),
1325 sync_on_finish_(args.sync_on_finish),
1326 num_outstanding_ops_(0) {
1327 // We start the entire execution in iteration 0 of the root frame
1328 // so let us create the root frame and the state for iteration 0.
1329 // We assume root_frame_->frame_name.empty().
1330 root_frame_ = new FrameState(impl_, 1);
1331 root_frame_->frame_id = 0; // must be 0
1332 root_frame_->InitializeFrameInfo(root_frame_->frame_name);
1333
1334 // Initialize iteration 0.
1335 root_frame_->iterations.resize(root_frame_->max_parallel_iterations);
1336 root_frame_->iterations[0] = new IterationState(
1337 root_frame_->pending_counts, root_frame_->total_input_tensors);
1338
1339 outstanding_frames_.insert({root_frame_->frame_name, root_frame_});
1340}
1341
1342ExecutorState::~ExecutorState() {
1343 for (auto name_frame : outstanding_frames_) {
1344 delete name_frame.second;
1345 }
1346 for (auto it : device_context_map_) {
1347 it->Unref();
1348 }
1349 delete slice_reader_cache_;
1350}
1351
1352Status ExecutorImpl::BuildControlFlowInfo(const Graph* g,
1353 ControlFlowInfo* cf_info) {
1354 const int num_nodes = g->num_node_ids();
1355 cf_info->frame_names.resize(num_nodes);
1356 std::vector<Node*> parent_nodes;
1357 parent_nodes.resize(num_nodes);
1358 std::vector<bool> visited;
1359 visited.resize(num_nodes);
1360
1361 string frame_name;
1362 std::deque<Node*> ready;
1363
1364 // Initialize with the root nodes.
1365 for (Node* n : g->nodes()) {
1366 if (n->in_edges().empty()) {
1367 visited[n->id()] = true;
1368 cf_info->unique_frame_names.insert(frame_name);
1369 ready.push_back(n);
1370 }
1371 }
1372
1373 while (!ready.empty()) {
1374 Node* curr_node = ready.front();
1375 int curr_id = curr_node->id();
1376 ready.pop_front();
1377
1378 Node* parent = nullptr;
1379 if (IsEnter(curr_node)) {
1380 // Enter a child frame.
1381 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1382 GetNodeAttr(curr_node->attrs(), "frame_name", &frame_name));
1383 parent = curr_node;
1384 } else if (IsExit(curr_node)) {
1385 // Exit to the parent frame.
1386 parent = parent_nodes[curr_id];
1387 frame_name = cf_info->frame_names[parent->id()];
1388 parent = parent_nodes[parent->id()];
1389 } else {
1390 parent = parent_nodes[curr_id];
1391 frame_name = cf_info->frame_names[curr_id];
1392 }
1393
1394 for (const Edge* out_edge : curr_node->out_edges()) {
1395 Node* out = out_edge->dst();
1396 const int out_id = out->id();
1397
1398 // Add to ready queue if not visited.
1399 bool is_visited = visited[out_id];
1400 if (!is_visited) {
1401 ready.push_back(out);
1402 visited[out_id] = true;
1403
1404 // Process the node 'out'.
1405 cf_info->frame_names[out_id] = frame_name;
1406 parent_nodes[out_id] = parent;
1407 cf_info->unique_frame_names.insert(frame_name);
1408 }
1409 }
1410 }
1411
1412 return Status::OK();
1413}
1414
1415void ExecutorImpl::InitializePending(const Graph* graph,
1416 const ControlFlowInfo& cf_info) {
1417 for (auto& it : cf_info.unique_frame_names) {
1418 FrameInfo* finfo = EnsureFrameInfo(it);
1419 PendingCounts* counts = new PendingCounts(finfo->pending_counts_layout);
1420 DCHECK_EQ(finfo->pending_counts, nullptr);
1421 finfo->pending_counts = counts;
1422 }
1423 for (const Node* n : graph->nodes()) {
1424 const int id = n->id();
1425 const string& name = cf_info.frame_names[id];
1426 size_t max_pending, max_dead;
1427 GetMaxPendingCounts(n, &max_pending, &max_dead);
1428 const NodeItem* item = gview_.node(id);
1429 PendingCounts* counts = EnsureFrameInfo(name)->pending_counts;
1430 counts->set_initial_count(item->pending_id, max_pending);
1431 }
1432}
1433
1434void ExecutorState::RunAsync(Executor::DoneCallback done) {
1435 const Graph* graph = impl_->graph_.get();
1436 TaggedNodeSeq ready;
1437
1438 // Ask the device to fill in the device context map.
1439 Device* device = impl_->params_.device;
1440 const Status fill_status =
1441 device->FillContextMap(graph, &device_context_map_);
1442 if (!fill_status.ok()) {
1443 done(fill_status);
1444 return;
1445 }
1446
1447 // Initialize the ready queue.
1448 for (const Node* n : impl_->root_nodes_) {
1449 DCHECK_EQ(n->in_edges().size(), 0);
1450 ready.push_back(TaggedNode{n, root_frame_, 0, false});
1451 }
1452 if (ready.empty()) {
1453 done(Status::OK());
1454 } else {
1455 num_outstanding_ops_ = ready.size();
1456 root_frame_->iterations[0]->outstanding_ops = ready.size();
1457 done_cb_ = std::move(done);
1458 // Schedule to run all the ready ops in thread pool.
1459 ScheduleReady(ready, nullptr);
1460 }
1461}
1462
1463// State kept alive for executing an asynchronous node in another
1464// thread. NOTE: We need to make a copy of p.input,
1465// p.input_device_contexts, and p.input_alloc_attrs for asynchronous
1466// kernels because OpKernelContext methods like input_type(i) needs
1467// the param points to valid input type vector. It's not an issue for
1468// sync kernels because these vectors are kept on the stack.
1469struct ExecutorState::AsyncState {
1470 AsyncState(const OpKernelContext::Params& p, const TaggedNode& _tagged_node,
1471 const NodeItem* _item, Entry* _first_input,
1472 NodeExecStatsWrapper* _stats)
1473 : saved_inputs(*p.inputs),
1474 saved_input_device_contexts(*p.input_device_contexts),
1475 saved_input_alloc_attrs(*p.input_alloc_attrs),
1476 params(p),
1477 tagged_node(_tagged_node),
1478 item(_item),
1479 first_input(_first_input),
1480 // ParamsButClearingEigenGPUDevice does equivalent of
1481 // params.eigen_gpu_device = nullptr;
1482 ctx(ParamsButClearingEigenGPUDevice(&params), item->num_outputs),
1483 stats(_stats) {
1484 params.inputs = &saved_inputs;
1485 params.input_device_contexts = &saved_input_device_contexts;
1486 params.input_alloc_attrs = &saved_input_alloc_attrs;
1487 }
1488
1489 TensorValueVec saved_inputs;
1490 DeviceContextVec saved_input_device_contexts;
1491 AllocatorAttributeVec saved_input_alloc_attrs;
1492 OpKernelContext::Params params;
1493 TaggedNode tagged_node;
1494 const NodeItem* item;
1495 Entry* first_input;
1496 OpKernelContext ctx;
1497 NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats;
1498
1499 private:
1500 OpKernelContext::Params* ParamsButClearingEigenGPUDevice(
1501 OpKernelContext::Params* p) {
1502 // Ensure OpKernelContext constructor will make a new eigen GPU device if
1503 // necessary.
1504 p->eigen_gpu_device = nullptr; // Force allocation
1505 return p;
1506 }
1507};
1508
1509void ExecutorState::Process(TaggedNode tagged_node, int64 scheduled_usec) {
1510 const GraphView& gview = impl_->gview_;
1511 TaggedNodeSeq ready;
1512 TaggedNodeReadyQueue inline_ready;
1513
1514 // Parameters passed to OpKernel::Compute.
1515 TensorValueVec inputs;
1516 DeviceContextVec input_device_contexts;
1517 AllocatorAttributeVec input_alloc_attrs;
1518
1519 OpKernelContext::Params params;
1520 params.step_id = step_id_;
1521 Device* device = impl_->params_.device;
1522 params.device = device;
1523 params.log_memory = log_memory_;
1524 params.record_tensor_accesses = impl_->device_record_tensor_accesses_;
1525 params.rendezvous = rendezvous_;
1526 params.session_state = session_state_;
1527 params.tensor_store = tensor_store_;
1528 params.cancellation_manager = cancellation_manager_;
1529 params.call_frame = call_frame_;
1530 params.function_library = impl_->params_.function_library;
1531 params.resource_manager = device->resource_manager();
1532 params.step_container = step_container_;
1533 params.slice_reader_cache = slice_reader_cache_;
1534 params.inputs = &inputs;
1535 params.input_device_contexts = &input_device_contexts;
1536 params.input_alloc_attrs = &input_alloc_attrs;
1537 params.runner = &runner_;
1538 params.stats_collector = stats_collector_;
1539
1540 Status s;
1541 NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats = nullptr;
1542 EntryVector outputs;
1543 bool completed = false;
1544 inline_ready.push_back(tagged_node);
1545 while (!inline_ready.empty()) {
1546 tagged_node = inline_ready.front();
1547 inline_ready.pop_front();
1548 const Node* node = tagged_node.node;
1549 FrameState* input_frame = tagged_node.input_frame;
1550 const int64 input_iter = tagged_node.input_iter;
1551 const int id = node->id();
1552 const NodeItem& item = *gview.node(id);
1553
1554 // TODO(misard) Replace with a finer-grain enabling flag once we
1555 // add better optional debugging support.
1556 if (vlog_ && VLOG_IS_ON(1)) {
1557 mutex_lock l(input_frame->mu);
1558 input_frame->GetIteration(input_iter)->mark_started(item.pending_id);
1559 }
1560
1561 // Set the device_context for this node id, if it exists.
1562 if (id < device_context_map_.size()) {
1563 params.op_device_context = device_context_map_[id];
1564 }
1565
1566 params.track_allocations = false;
1567 stats = nullptr;
1568 if (stats_collector_ && !tagged_node.is_dead) {
1569 // track allocations if and only if we are collecting statistics
1570 params.track_allocations = true;
1571 stats = new NodeExecStatsWrapper;
1572 stats->stats()->set_node_name(node->name());
1573 nodestats::SetScheduled(stats, scheduled_usec);
1574 nodestats::SetAllStart(stats);
1575 }
1576
1577 if (vlog_) {
1578 VLOG(1) << "Process node: " << id << " step " << params.step_id << " "
1579 << SummarizeNode(*node) << " is dead: " << tagged_node.is_dead;
1580 }
1581
1582 Entry* input_tensors = GetInputTensors(input_frame, input_iter);
1583 Entry* first_input = input_tensors + item.input_start;
1584 outputs.clear();
1585
1586 TensorReferenceVector accessed_tensors;
1587 DeviceContext* device_context = nullptr;
1588 // Only execute this node if it is not dead or it is a send/recv
1589 // transfer node. For transfer nodes, we need to propagate the "dead"
1590 // bit even when the node is dead.
1591 bool launched_asynchronously = false;
1592 if (tagged_node.is_dead && !IsTransferNode(node)) {
1593 outputs.resize(item.num_outputs);
1594 } else {
1595 // Prepares inputs.
1596 bool is_input_dead = false;
1597 s = PrepareInputs(item, first_input, &inputs, &input_device_contexts,
1598 &input_alloc_attrs, &is_input_dead);
1599 if (!s.ok()) {
1600 // Clear inputs.
1601 int num_inputs = item.num_inputs;
1602 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1603 (first_input + i)->ClearVal();
1604 }
1605 MaybeMarkCompleted(input_frame, input_iter, id);
1606 // Continue to process the nodes in 'inline_ready'.
1607 completed = NodeDone(s, item.node, ready, stats, &inline_ready);
1608 continue;
1609 }
1610
1611 // Set up compute params.
1612 OpKernel* op_kernel = item.kernel;
1613 params.op_kernel = op_kernel;
1614 params.frame_iter = FrameAndIter(input_frame->frame_id, input_iter);
1615 params.is_input_dead = is_input_dead;
1616 params.output_attr_array = item.output_attrs();
1617 params.forward_from_array = nullptr; // later: item.forward_from();
1618
1619 if (item.kernel_is_async) {
1620 // Asynchronous computes.
1621 AsyncOpKernel* async = item.kernel->AsAsync();
1622 DCHECK(async != nullptr);
1623 launched_asynchronously = true;
1624 AsyncState* state =
1625 new AsyncState(params, tagged_node, &item, first_input, stats);
1626
1627 auto done = [this, state]() {
1628 Device* device = impl_->params_.device;
1629 NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats = state->stats; // Shorthand
1630 Entry* first_input = state->first_input; // Shorthand
1631
1632 nodestats::SetOpEnd(stats);
1633 EntryVector outputs;
1634 Status s = ProcessOutputs(*state->item, &state->ctx, &outputs, stats);
1635 nodestats::SetMemory(stats, &state->ctx);
1636 if (vlog_) {
1637 VLOG(2) << "Async kernel done: " << state->item->node->id()
1638 << " step " << step_id_ << " "
1639 << SummarizeNode(*state->item->node)
1640 << " is dead: " << state->tagged_node.is_dead;
1641 }
1642
1643 // Clears inputs.
1644 const int num_inputs = state->item->num_inputs;
1645 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1646 (first_input + i)->ClearVal();
1647 }
1648 FrameState* input_frame = state->tagged_node.input_frame;
1649 const int64 input_iter = state->tagged_node.input_iter;
1650 const int id = state->tagged_node.node->id();
1651 MaybeMarkCompleted(input_frame, input_iter, id);
1652 TaggedNodeSeq ready;
1653 if (s.ok()) {
1654 PropagateOutputs(state->tagged_node, state->item, &outputs, &ready);
1655 }
1656 outputs.clear();
1657 if (s.ok() && impl_->device_record_tensor_accesses_) {
1658 // Get the list of all tensors accessed during the execution
1659 TensorReferenceVector accessed;
1660 state->ctx.retrieve_accessed_tensors(&accessed);
1661 nodestats::SetReferencedTensors(stats, accessed);
1662 // callee takes ownership of the vector
1663 device->ConsumeListOfAccessedTensors(state->ctx.op_device_context(),
1664 accessed);
1665 }
1666 const bool completed =
1667 NodeDone(s, state->item->node, ready, stats, nullptr);
1668 delete state;
1669 if (completed) Finish();
1670 };
1671 nodestats::SetOpStart(stats);
1672 device->ComputeAsync(async, &state->ctx, done);
1673 } else {
1674 // Synchronous computes.
1675 OpKernelContext ctx(&params, item.num_outputs);
1676 nodestats::SetOpStart(stats);
1677 device->Compute(CHECK_NOTNULL(op_kernel), &ctx);
1678 nodestats::SetOpEnd(stats);
1679 s = ProcessOutputs(item, &ctx, &outputs, stats);
1680 if (s.ok() && impl_->device_record_tensor_accesses_) {
1681 // Get the list of all tensors accessed during the execution
1682 ctx.retrieve_accessed_tensors(&accessed_tensors);
1683 device_context = ctx.op_device_context();
1684 }
1685 nodestats::SetMemory(stats, &ctx);
1686 }
1687 }
1688
1689 if (!launched_asynchronously) {
1690 if (vlog_) {
1691 VLOG(2) << "Synchronous kernel done: " << id << " step "
1692 << params.step_id << " " << SummarizeNode(*node)
1693 << " is dead: " << tagged_node.is_dead;
1694 }
1695
1696 // Clears inputs.
1697 const int num_inputs = item.num_inputs;
1698 for (int i = 0; i < num_inputs; ++i) {
1699 (first_input + i)->ClearVal();
1700 }
1701 MaybeMarkCompleted(input_frame, input_iter, id);
1702 // Propagates outputs.
1703 if (s.ok()) {
1704 PropagateOutputs(tagged_node, &item, &outputs, &ready);
1705 }
1706 outputs.clear();
1707 if (!accessed_tensors.empty()) {
1708 nodestats::SetReferencedTensors(stats, accessed_tensors);
1709 // device_context is set above in synchronous computes
1710 device->ConsumeListOfAccessedTensors(device_context, accessed_tensors);
1711 }
1712 if (stats) {
1713 scheduled_usec = nodestats::NowInUsec();
1714 }
1715 // Postprocess.
1716 completed = NodeDone(s, item.node, ready, stats, &inline_ready);
1717 }
1718 } // while !inline_ready.empty()
1719
1720 // This thread of computation is done if completed = true.
1721 if (completed) Finish();
1722}
1723
1724Status ExecutorState::PrepareInputs(const NodeItem& item, Entry* first_input,
1725 TensorValueVec* inputs,
1726 DeviceContextVec* input_device_contexts,
1727 AllocatorAttributeVec* input_alloc_attrs,
1728 bool* is_input_dead) {
1729 const Node* node = item.node;
1730
1731 inputs->clear();
1732 inputs->resize(item.num_inputs);
1733 input_device_contexts->clear();
1734 input_device_contexts->resize(item.num_inputs);
1735 input_alloc_attrs->clear();
1736 input_alloc_attrs->resize(item.num_inputs);
1737
1738 *is_input_dead = false;
1739
1740 bool is_merge = item.is_merge;
1741 for (int i = 0; i < item.num_inputs; ++i) {
1742 const bool expect_ref = IsRefType(item.input_type(i));
1743 Entry* entry = first_input + i;
1744 (*input_device_contexts)[i] = entry->device_context;
1745 (*input_alloc_attrs)[i] = entry->alloc_attr;
1746
1747 // i-th input.
1748 TensorValue* inp = &(*inputs)[i];
1749
1750 // Only merge and transfer nodes can have no-value inputs.
1751 if (!entry->has_value) {
1752 if (!is_merge) {
1753 DCHECK(IsTransferNode(node)) << node->name() << " - input " << i;
1754 DCHECK(!entry->val_field_is_set) << node->name() << " - input " << i;
1755 entry->has_value = true;
1756 entry->val_field_is_set = true;
1757 entry->val.Init(*kEmptyTensor);
1758 inp->tensor = entry->val.get();
1759 *is_input_dead = true;
1760 }
1761 continue;
1762 }
1763 if (entry->ref == nullptr) {
1764 if (expect_ref) {
1765 return AttachDef(
1766 errors::InvalidArgument(i, "-th input expects a ref type"),
1767 item.kernel->def());
1768 }
1769 inp->tensor = entry->val.get();
1770 } else {
1771 {
1772 mutex_lock ml(*entry->ref_mu);
1773 if (!entry->ref->IsInitialized() && !IsInitializationOp(item.node)) {
1774 return AttachDef(errors::FailedPrecondition(
1775 "Attempting to use uninitialized value ",
1776 item.kernel->requested_input(i)),
1777 item.kernel->def());
1778 }
1779 }
1780 if (expect_ref) {
1781 inp->mutex_if_ref = entry->ref_mu;
1782 inp->tensor = entry->ref;
1783 } else {
1784 // Automatically deref the tensor ref when the op expects a
1785 // tensor but is given a ref to a tensor. Need to deref it
1786 // under the mutex.
1787 {
1788 mutex_lock l(*(entry->ref_mu));
1789 DCHECK(!entry->val_field_is_set);
1790 entry->val.Init(*entry->ref);
1791 entry->val_field_is_set = true;
1792 }
1793 entry->ref = nullptr;
1794 entry->ref_mu = nullptr;
1795
1796 inp->tensor = entry->val.get();
1797 // The dtype of entry->ref could have been changed by another operation
1798 // that ran after the operation that "produced" it executed, so
1799 // re-validate that the type of the dereferenced tensor matches the
1800 // expected input type.
1801 if (item.input_type(i) != inp->tensor->dtype()) {
1802 return AttachDef(
1803 errors::InvalidArgument(
1804 i, "-th input expects type ",
1805 DataTypeString(item.input_type(i)),
1806 " but automatically dereferenced input tensor has type ",
1807 DataTypeString(inp->tensor->dtype())),
1808 item.kernel->def());
1809 }
1810 }
1811 }
1812 }
1813 return Status::OK();
1814}
1815
1816Status ExecutorState::ProcessOutputs(const NodeItem& item, OpKernelContext* ctx,
1817 EntryVector* outputs,
1818 NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats) {
1819 const Node* node = item.node;
1820 DCHECK_EQ(0, outputs->size());
1821 outputs->resize(item.num_outputs);
1822
1823 Status s = ctx->status();
1824 if (!s.ok()) {
1825 s = AttachDef(s, item.kernel->def());
1826 // TODO(misard) Replace with a finer-grain enabling flag once we
1827 // add better optional debugging support.
1828 if (vlog_ && VLOG_IS_ON(1)) {
1829 LOG(WARNING) << this << " Compute status: " << s;
1830 DumpState();
1831 }
1832 if (s.code() == error::RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED) {
1833 if (stats_collector_) {
1834 string err = stats_collector_->ReportAllocsOnResourceExhausted(
1835 s.error_message());
1836 s = Status(s.code(), strings::StrCat(s.error_message(), err));
1837 } else {
1838 s = Status(
1839 s.code(),
1840 strings::StrCat(
1841 s.error_message(),
1842 "\nHint: If you want to see a list of allocated tensors when "
1843 "OOM happens, add report_tensor_allocations_upon_oom "
1844 "to RunOptions for current allocation info.\n"));
1845 }
1846 }
1847 return s;
1848 }
1849
1850 // Get the device_context for this node id, if it exists.
1851 DeviceContext* device_context = nullptr;
1852 if (node->id() < device_context_map_.size()) {
1853 device_context = device_context_map_[node->id()];
1854 }
1855
1856 // Experimental: debugger (tfdb) access to intermediate node completion.
1857 if (item.num_outputs == 0 && impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb != nullptr) {
1858 // If the node has no output, invoke the callback with output slot set to
1859 // -1, signifying that this is a no-output node.
1860 s.Update(impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb(item.node->name(), -1, nullptr,
1861 false, ctx));
1862 }
1863
1864 for (int i = 0; i < item.num_outputs; ++i) {
1865 const TensorValue val = ctx->release_output(i);
1866 if (*ctx->is_output_dead() || val.tensor == nullptr) {
1867 // Unless it's a Switch or a Recv, the node must produce a
1868 // tensor value at i-th output.
1869 if (!IsSwitch(node) && !IsRecv(node)) {
1870 s.Update(errors::Internal("Missing ", i, "-th output from ",
1871 SummarizeNode(*node)));
1872 }
1873 } else {
1874 Entry* out = &((*outputs)[i]);
1875
1876 // Set the device context of the output entry.
1877 out->device_context = device_context;
1878
1879 // Set the allocator attributes of the output entry.
1880 out->alloc_attr = ctx->output_alloc_attr(i);
1881
1882 // Sanity check of output tensor types.
1883 DataType dtype;
1884 if (val.is_ref()) {
1885 mutex_lock ml(*val.mutex_if_ref);
1886 dtype = MakeRefType(val->dtype());
1887 } else {
1888 dtype = val->dtype();
1889 }
1890 if (dtype == item.output_type(i)) {
1891 if (stats && val.tensor->IsInitialized()) {
1892 nodestats::SetOutput(stats, i, val.tensor);
1893 }
1894 if (val.is_ref()) {
1895 out->has_value = true;
1896 out->ref = val.tensor;
1897 out->ref_mu = val.mutex_if_ref;
1898 if (log_memory_) {
1899 Tensor to_log;
1900 {
1901 // Dereference the tensor under the lock.
1902 mutex_lock l(*out->ref_mu);
1903 to_log = *out->ref;
1904 }
1905 LogMemory::RecordTensorOutput(ctx->op_kernel().name(),
1906 ctx->step_id(), i, to_log);
1907 }
1908
1909 // Experimental: debugger (tfdb) access to intermediate node
1910 // outputs.
1911 if (impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb != nullptr) {
1912 s.Update(impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb(item.node->name(), i,
1913 out->ref, true, ctx));
1914 }
1915 } else {
1916 // NOTE that std::move is used here, so val.tensor goes to
1917 // uninitialized state (val.tensor->IsInitialized return false).
1918 DCHECK(!out->val_field_is_set);
1919 out->has_value = true;
1920 out->val_field_is_set = true;
1921 out->val.Init(std::move(*val.tensor));
1922 if (log_memory_) {
1923 LogMemory::RecordTensorOutput(ctx->op_kernel().name(),
1924 ctx->step_id(), i, *out->val);
1925 }
1926
1927 // Experimental: debugger access to intermediate node outputs.
1928 if (impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb != nullptr) {
1929 s.Update(impl_->params_.node_outputs_cb(
1930 item.node->name(), i, out->val.get(), false, ctx));
1931 }
1932 }
1933 } else {
1934 s.Update(errors::Internal("Output ", i, " of type ",
1935 DataTypeString(dtype),
1936 " does not match declared output type ",
1937 DataTypeString(item.output_type(i)),
1938 " for node ", SummarizeNode(*node)));
1939 }
1940 }
1941 if (!val.is_ref()) {
1942 // If OpKernelContext returns outputs via pass-by-value, we
1943 // don't need this trouble.
1944 delete val.tensor;
1945 }
1946 }
1947 return s;
1948}
1949
1950void ExecutorState::PropagateOutputs(const TaggedNode& tagged_node,
1951 const NodeItem* item, EntryVector* outputs,
1952 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
1953 const Node* node = tagged_node.node;
1954 FrameState* input_frame = tagged_node.input_frame;
1955 const int64 input_iter = tagged_node.input_iter;
1956 const bool is_dead = tagged_node.is_dead;
1957
1958 // Propagates outputs along out edges, and puts newly ready nodes
1959 // into the ready queue.
1960 ready->clear();
1961 bool is_frame_done = false;
1962 FrameState* output_frame = input_frame;
1963 int64 output_iter = input_iter;
1964
1965 if (!item->is_enter_exit_or_next_iter) {
1966 // Fast path for nodes types that don't need special handling
1967 DCHECK_EQ(input_frame, output_frame);
1968 // Normal path for most nodes
1969 mutex_lock l(input_frame->mu);
1970 output_frame->ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, output_iter, outputs, ready);
1971 is_frame_done = input_frame->DecrementOutstandingOpsLocked(
1972 &impl_->gview_, input_iter, ready);
1973 } else if (item->is_enter) {
1974 bool is_constant;
1975 const Status s = GetNodeAttr(node->attrs(), "is_constant", &is_constant);
1976 DCHECK(s.ok()) << s;
1977 FindOrCreateChildFrame(input_frame, input_iter, node, &output_frame);
1978 output_iter = 0;
1979 {
1980 const NodeItem* item = impl_->gview_.node(node->id());
1981 mutex_lock l(output_frame->mu);
1982 if (is_constant) {
1983 // Propagate to all active iterations if this is a loop invariant.
1984 output_frame->AddLoopInv(item, (*outputs)[0], ready);
1985 } else {
1986 output_frame->ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, output_iter, outputs, ready);
1987 }
1988 output_frame->num_pending_inputs--;
1989 }
1990 is_frame_done =
1991 input_frame->DecrementOutstandingOps(&impl_->gview_, input_iter, ready);
1992 } else if (item->is_exit) {
1993 if (is_dead) {
1994 mutex_lock l(input_frame->mu);
1995 // Stop and remember this node if it is a dead exit.
1996 if (input_iter == input_frame->iteration_count) {
1997 input_frame->dead_exits.push_back(node);
1998 }
1999 is_frame_done = input_frame->DecrementOutstandingOpsLocked(
2000 &impl_->gview_, input_iter, ready);
2001 } else {
2002 output_frame = input_frame->parent_frame;
2003 output_iter = input_frame->parent_iter;
2004 {
2005 mutex_lock l(output_frame->mu);
2006 output_frame->ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, output_iter, outputs, ready);
2007 }
2008 is_frame_done = input_frame->DecrementOutstandingOps(&impl_->gview_,
2009 input_iter, ready);
2010 }
2011 } else {
2012 DCHECK(IsNextIteration(node));
2013 mutex_lock l(input_frame->mu);
2014 if (is_dead) {
2015 // Stop the deadness propagation.
2016 output_frame = nullptr;
2017 } else {
2018 if (input_iter == input_frame->iteration_count &&
2019 input_frame->num_outstanding_iterations ==
2020 input_frame->max_parallel_iterations) {
2021 // Reached the maximum for parallel iterations.
2022 input_frame->next_iter_roots.push_back({node, (*outputs)[0]});
2023 output_frame = nullptr;
2024 } else {
2025 // If this is a new iteration, start it.
2026 if (input_iter == input_frame->iteration_count) {
2027 input_frame->IncrementIteration(&impl_->gview_, ready);
2028 }
2029 output_iter = input_iter + 1;
2030 }
2031 }
2032 if (output_frame != nullptr) {
2033 // This is the case when node is not Enter, Exit, or NextIteration.
2034 DCHECK(input_frame == output_frame);
2035 output_frame->ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, output_iter, outputs, ready);
2036 }
2037 is_frame_done = input_frame->DecrementOutstandingOpsLocked(
2038 &impl_->gview_, input_iter, ready);
2039 }
2040
2041 // At this point, this node is completely done. We also know if the
2042 // completion of this node makes its frame completed.
2043 if (is_frame_done) {
2044 FrameState* parent_frame = input_frame->parent_frame;
2045 const int64 parent_iter = input_frame->parent_iter;
2046 DeleteFrame(input_frame, ready);
2047 if (parent_frame != nullptr) {
2048 // The completion of frame may cause completions in its parent frame.
2049 // So clean things up recursively.
2050 CleanupFramesIterations(parent_frame, parent_iter, ready);
2051 }
2052 }
2053}
2054
2055bool ExecutorState::NodeDone(const Status& s, const Node* node,
2056 const TaggedNodeSeq& ready,
2057 NodeExecStatsWrapper* stats,
2058 TaggedNodeReadyQueue* inline_ready) {
2059 nodestats::SetAllEnd(stats);
2060 if (stats_collector_ != nullptr && !SetTimelineLabel(node, stats)) {
2061 // Only record non-transfer nodes.
2062 // Transfers 'stats' ownership to 'stats_collector_'.
2063 stats_collector_->Save(impl_->params_.device->name(), stats);
2064 } else if (stats) {
2065 delete stats;
2066 }
2067
2068 bool abort_run = false;
2069 if (!s.ok()) {
2070 // Some error happened. This thread of computation is done.
2071 mutex_lock l(mu_);
2072 if (status_.ok()) {
2073 abort_run = true;
2074 status_ = s;
2075 }
2076 }
2077 if (abort_run) {
2078 TRACEPRINTF("StartAbort: %s", s.ToString().c_str());
2079 if (rendezvous_) {
2080 rendezvous_->StartAbort(s);
2081 }
2082 if (cancellation_manager_) {
2083 cancellation_manager_->StartCancel();
2084 }
2085 }
2086
2087 bool completed = false;
2088 const size_t ready_size = ready.size();
2089 if (ready_size == 0 || !s.ok()) {
2090 completed = (num_outstanding_ops_.fetch_sub(1) == 1);
2091 } else if (ready_size > 1) {
2092 num_outstanding_ops_.fetch_add(ready_size - 1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
2093 }
2094
2095 // Schedule the ready nodes in 'ready'.
2096 if (s.ok()) {
2097 ScheduleReady(ready, inline_ready);
2098 }
2099 return completed;
2100}
2101
2102void ExecutorState::ScheduleReady(const TaggedNodeSeq& ready,
2103 TaggedNodeReadyQueue* inline_ready) {
2104 if (ready.empty()) return;
2105
2106 int64 scheduled_usec = 0;
2107 if (stats_collector_) {
2108 scheduled_usec = nodestats::NowInUsec();
2109 }
2110 if (inline_ready == nullptr) {
2111 // Schedule to run all the ready ops in thread pool.
2112 for (auto& tagged_node : ready) {
2113 runner_([=]() { Process(tagged_node, scheduled_usec); });
2114 }
2115 return;
2116 }
2117 const GraphView& gview = impl_->gview_;
2118 const TaggedNode* curr_expensive_node = nullptr;
2119 for (auto& tagged_node : ready) {
2120 const NodeItem& item = *gview.node(tagged_node.node->id());
2121 if (tagged_node.is_dead || !item.kernel_is_expensive) {
2122 // Inline this inexpensive node.
2123 inline_ready->push_back(tagged_node);
2124 } else {
2125 if (curr_expensive_node) {
2126 // Dispatch to another thread since there is plenty of work to
2127 // do for this thread.
2128 runner_(std::bind(&ExecutorState::Process, this, *curr_expensive_node,
2129 scheduled_usec));
2130 }
2131 curr_expensive_node = &tagged_node;
2132 }
2133 }
2134 if (curr_expensive_node) {
2135 if (inline_ready->empty()) {
2136 // Tail recursion optimization
2137 inline_ready->push_back(*curr_expensive_node);
2138 } else {
2139 // There are inline nodes to run already. We dispatch this expensive
2140 // node to other thread.
2141 runner_(std::bind(&ExecutorState::Process, this, *curr_expensive_node,
2142 scheduled_usec));
2143 }
2144 }
2145}

2147inline void ExecutorState::MaybeMarkCompleted(FrameState* frame, int64 iter,
2148 int64 node_id) {
2149 // TODO(misard) Replace with a finer-grain enabling flag once we
2150 // add better optional debugging support.
2151 if (vlog_ && VLOG_IS_ON(1)) {
2152 const NodeItem* item = impl_->gview_.node(node_id);
2153 mutex_lock l(frame->mu);
2154 frame->GetIteration(iter)->mark_completed(item->pending_id);
2155 }
2156}

2158const Tensor* ExecutorState::GetTensorValueForDump(const Entry& input) {
2159 if (!input.has_value) {
2160 return kEmptyTensor;
2161 } else if (input.ref == nullptr) {
2162 return input.val.get();
2163 } else {
2164 return input.ref;
2165 }
2166}

2168void ExecutorState::DumpPendingNodeState(
2169 const int node_id, const Entry* input_vector,
2170 const bool show_nodes_with_no_ready_inputs) {
2171 const NodeItem& node_item = *impl_->gview_.node(node_id);
2172 const Node& node = *node_item.node;
2173 const int input_base = node_item.input_start;
2174 if (!show_nodes_with_no_ready_inputs) {
2175 bool has_ready_input = false;
2176 for (int i = 0; i < node.num_inputs(); ++i) {
2177 const Entry& input = input_vector[input_base + i];
2178 const Tensor* tensor = GetTensorValueForDump(input);
2179 if (tensor->IsInitialized()) {
2180 has_ready_input = true;
2181 break;
2182 }
2183 }
2184 if (!has_ready_input) {
2185 return;
2186 }
2187 }
2188 LOG(WARNING) << " Pending Node: " << node.DebugString();
2189 for (int i = 0; i < node.num_inputs(); ++i) {
2190 const Entry& input = input_vector[input_base + i];
2191 const Tensor* tensor = GetTensorValueForDump(input);
2192 if (tensor->IsInitialized()) {
2193 LOG(WARNING) << " Input " << i << ": "
2194 << strings::StrCat(
2195 "Tensor<type: ", DataTypeString(tensor->dtype()),
2196 " shape: ", tensor->shape().DebugString(), ">");
2197 } else {
2198 LOG(WARNING) << " Input " << i << ": not present";
2199 }
2200 }
2201}

2203void ExecutorState::DumpActiveNodeState(const int node_id,
2204 const Entry* input_vector) {
2205 const NodeItem& node_item = *impl_->gview_.node(node_id);
2206 const Node& node = *node_item.node;
2207 LOG(WARNING) << " Active Node: " << node.DebugString();
2208 const int input_base = node_item.input_start;
2209 for (int i = 0; i < node.num_inputs(); ++i) {
2210 const Entry& input = input_vector[input_base + i];
2211 const Tensor* tensor = GetTensorValueForDump(input);
2212 if (tensor->IsInitialized()) {
2213 LOG(WARNING) << " Input " << i << ": "
2214 << strings::StrCat(
2215 "Tensor<type: ", DataTypeString(tensor->dtype()),
2216 " shape: ", tensor->shape().DebugString(), ">");
2217 } else {
2218 LOG(WARNING) << " Input " << i << ": not present";
2219 }
2220 }
