2222
2223void ExecutorState::DumpIterationState(const FrameState* frame,
2224 IterationState* iteration) {
2225 const std::vector<const Node*>* nodes = frame->nodes;
2226 // Dump any waiting nodes that are holding on to tensors.
2227 for (const Node* node : *nodes) {
2228 const int node_id = node->id();
2229 PendingCounts::Handle pending_id = impl_->gview_.node(node_id)->pending_id;
2230 if (iteration->node_state(pending_id) == PendingCounts::PENDING_NOTREADY ||
2231 iteration->node_state(pending_id) == PendingCounts::PENDING_READY) {
2232 DumpPendingNodeState(node_id, iteration->input_tensors, false);
2233 }
2234 }
2235 // Then the active nodes.
2236 for (const Node* node : *nodes) {
2237 const int node_id = node->id();
2238 PendingCounts::Handle pending_id = impl_->gview_.node(node_id)->pending_id;
2239 if (iteration->node_state(pending_id) == PendingCounts::STARTED) {
2240 DumpActiveNodeState(node_id, iteration->input_tensors);
2241 }
2242 }
2243 // Show all input tensors in use.
2244 const int total_input_tensors = frame->total_input_tensors;
2245 size_t total_bytes = 0;
2246 for (int i = 0; i < total_input_tensors; ++i) {
2247 const Entry& input = iteration->input_tensors[i];
2248 const Tensor* tensor = GetTensorValueForDump(input);
2249 if (tensor->IsInitialized()) {
2250 LOG(WARNING) << " Input " << i << ": "
2251 << strings::StrCat(
2252 "Tensor<type: ", DataTypeString(tensor->dtype()),
2253 " shape: ", tensor->shape().DebugString(),
2254 ", bytes: ", tensor->TotalBytes(), ">");
2255 total_bytes += tensor->TotalBytes();
2256 }
2257 }
2258 LOG(WARNING) << " Total bytes " << total_bytes;
2259}
2260
2261void ExecutorState::DumpState() {
2262 mutex_lock l(mu_);
2263 if (!dumped_on_error_) {
2264 LOG(WARNING) << "Dumping state";
2265 for (auto& frame : outstanding_frames_) {
2266 LOG(WARNING) << frame.first;
2267 FrameState* frame_state = frame.second;
2268 mutex_lock frame_lock(frame_state->mu);
2269 for (IterationState* iteration : frame_state->iterations) {
2270 LOG(WARNING) << " Iteration:";
2271 DumpIterationState(frame_state, iteration);
2272 }
2273 }
2274 dumped_on_error_ = true;
2275 }
2276}
2277
2278void ExecutorState::Finish() {
2279 mu_.lock();
2280 auto status = status_;
2281 auto done_cb = std::move(done_cb_);
2282 auto runner = std::move(runner_);
2283 mu_.unlock();
2284 if (sync_on_finish_ && status.ok()) {
2285 // Block until the device has finished all queued operations. For
2286 // devices like GPUs that continue to execute Ops after their Compute
2287 // methods have completed, this ensures that control is not returned to
2288 // the user until the step (and its side-effects) has actually completed.
2289 status = impl_->params_.device->Sync();
2290 }
2291 delete this;
2292 CHECK(done_cb != nullptr);
2293 runner([=]() { done_cb(status); });
2294}
2295
2296void ExecutorState::FindOrCreateChildFrame(FrameState* frame, int64 iter,
2297 const Node* node,
2298 FrameState** child) {
2299 // Get the child frame name.
2300 string enter_name;
2301 Status s = GetNodeAttr(node->attrs(), "frame_name", &enter_name);
2302 DCHECK(s.ok()) << s;
2303 const string child_name = MakeFrameName(frame, iter, enter_name);
2304
2305 {
2306 mutex_lock executor_lock(mu_);
2307 auto it = outstanding_frames_.find(child_name);
2308 if (it != outstanding_frames_.end()) {
2309 *child = it->second;
2310 return;
2311 }
2312 }
2313
2314 // Need to create a new frame instance.
2315 // Note that this new frame instance is created without any locks.
2316 if (vlog_) VLOG(2) << "Create frame: " << child_name;
2317
2318 int parallel_iters;
2319 s = GetNodeAttr(node->attrs(), "parallel_iterations", &parallel_iters);
2320 DCHECK(s.ok()) << s;
2321 FrameState* temp = new FrameState(impl_, parallel_iters);
2322 temp->frame_name = child_name;
2323 temp->frame_id = Hash64(child_name);
2324 temp->parent_frame = frame;
2325 temp->parent_iter = iter;
2326 temp->InitializeFrameInfo(enter_name);
2327
2328 // 'iterations' is a fixed-length circular buffer.
2329 temp->iterations.resize(temp->max_parallel_iterations + 1);
2330 // Initialize iteration 0.
2331 temp->iterations[0] =
2332 new IterationState(temp->pending_counts, temp->total_input_tensors);
2333
2334 {
2335 mutex_lock executor_lock(mu_);
2336 auto it = outstanding_frames_.find(child_name);
2337 if (it != outstanding_frames_.end()) {
2338 *child = it->second;
2339 } else {
2340 mutex_lock frame_lock(frame->mu);
2341 frame->GetIteration(iter)->outstanding_frame_count++;
2342 outstanding_frames_[child_name] = temp;
2343 *child = temp;
2344 temp = nullptr;
2345 }
2346 }
2347 delete temp; // Not used so delete it.
2348}
2349
2350void ExecutorState::DeleteFrame(FrameState* frame, TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2351 // First, propagate dead_exits (if any) to the parent frame.
2352 FrameState* parent_frame = frame->parent_frame;
2353 const int64 parent_iter = frame->parent_iter;
2354 if (parent_frame != nullptr) {
2355 mutex_lock parent_frame_lock(parent_frame->mu);
2356 // Propagate all the dead exits to the parent frame.
2357 mutex_lock this_frame_lock(frame->mu);
2358 for (const Node* node : frame->dead_exits) {
2359 auto parent_iter_state = parent_frame->GetIteration(parent_iter);
2360 for (const Edge* e : node->out_edges()) {
2361 const Node* dst_node = e->dst();
2362
2363 const auto dst_pending_id =
2364 impl_->gview_.node(dst_node->id())->pending_id;
2365
2366 // TODO(yuanbyu): We don't need this if we require the subgraph
2367 // given to an executor not to contain a sink node.
2368 if (dst_node->IsSink()) continue;
2369
2370 bool dst_dead = true;
2371 bool dst_ready = false;
2372 // We know this is a dead input to dst.
2373 if (IsMerge(dst_node)) {
2374 if (e->IsControlEdge()) {
2375 parent_iter_state->decrement_pending(dst_pending_id, 2);
2376 int count = parent_iter_state->pending(dst_pending_id);
2377 int dead_cnt = parent_iter_state->dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2378 dst_dead = (dead_cnt == dst_node->num_inputs());
2379 dst_ready = (count == 0) || ((count == 1) && dst_dead);
2380 } else {
2381 parent_iter_state->increment_dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2382 const int dead_cnt = parent_iter_state->dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2383 dst_dead = (dead_cnt == dst_node->num_inputs());
2384 dst_ready =
2385 (parent_iter_state->pending(dst_pending_id) == 1) && dst_dead;
2386 }
2387 } else {
2388 parent_iter_state->increment_dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2389 dst_ready =
2390 (parent_iter_state->decrement_pending(dst_pending_id, 1) == 0);
2391 }
2392 if (dst_ready) {
2393 if (IsControlTrigger(dst_node)) dst_dead = false;
2394 ready->push_back(
2395 TaggedNode(dst_node, parent_frame, parent_iter, dst_dead));
2396 parent_iter_state->outstanding_ops++;
2397 }
2398 }
2399 }
2400 }
2401
2402 // Delete the frame.
2403 const string& frame_name = frame->frame_name;
2404 if (vlog_) VLOG(2) << "Delete frame " << frame_name;
2405 {
2406 mutex_lock executor_lock(mu_);
2407 outstanding_frames_.erase(frame_name);
2408 }
2409 delete frame;
2410}
2411
2412void ExecutorState::CleanupFramesIterations(FrameState* frame, int64 iter,
2413 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2414 bool is_frame_done = false;
2415 {
2416 mutex_lock frame_lock(frame->mu);
2417 frame->GetIteration(iter)->outstanding_frame_count--;
2418 is_frame_done = frame->CleanupIterations(&impl_->gview_, iter, ready);
2419 }
2420 if (is_frame_done) {
2421 FrameState* parent_frame = frame->parent_frame;
2422 const int64 parent_iter = frame->parent_iter;
2423 DeleteFrame(frame, ready);
2424 if (parent_frame != nullptr) {
2425 // The completion of frame may cause completions in its parent frame.
2426 // So clean things up recursively.
2427 CleanupFramesIterations(parent_frame, parent_iter, ready);
2428 }
2429 }
2430}
2431
2432void ExecutorState::FrameState::ActivateNodes(const NodeItem* item,
2433 const bool is_dead, int64 iter,
2434 EntryVector* outputs,
2435 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2436 const GraphView& gview = executor->gview_;
2437 IterationState* iter_state = GetIteration(iter);
2438 const size_t num_output_edges = item->num_output_edges;
2439 const EdgeInfo* edges = item->output_edge_list();
2440 Entry* input_tensors = iter_state->input_tensors;
2441 for (size_t out_index = 0; out_index < num_output_edges; out_index++) {
2442 const EdgeInfo& e = edges[out_index];
2443 const int dst_id = e.dst_id;
2444 const NodeItem* dst_item = gview.node(dst_id);
2445 const PendingCounts::Handle dst_pending_id = dst_item->pending_id;
2446 const int src_slot = e.output_slot;
2447
2448 // TODO(yuanbyu): We don't need this if we require the subgraph
2449 // given to an executor not to contain a sink node.
2450 if (dst_item->is_sink) continue;
2451
2452 bool dst_dead = false;
2453 bool dst_ready = false;
2454 // True iff this input for dst is needed. We only set this input for
2455 // dst if this flag is true. This is needed to make the thread safety
2456 // analysis happy.
2457 const bool is_control_edge = (src_slot == Graph::kControlSlot);
2458 bool dst_need_input = !is_control_edge;
2459 if (dst_item->is_merge) {
2460 // A merge node is ready if all control inputs have arrived and either
2461 // a) a live data input becomes available or b) all data inputs are
2462 // dead. For Merge, pending's LSB is set iff a live data input has
2463 // arrived.
2464 if (is_control_edge) {
2465 iter_state->decrement_pending(dst_pending_id, 2);
2466 int count = iter_state->pending(dst_pending_id);
2467 int dead_cnt = iter_state->dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2468 dst_dead = (dead_cnt == dst_item->num_inputs);
2469 dst_ready = (count == 0) || ((count == 1) && dst_dead);
2470 } else {
2471 if ((*outputs)[src_slot].has_value) {
2472 // This is a live data input.
2473 int count = iter_state->pending(dst_pending_id);
2474 iter_state->mark_live(dst_pending_id);
2475 // Only the first live edge sets the input and (potentially)
2476 // triggers execution. The low bit of count is set if and
2477 // only if no live input has been used yet (mark_live clears
2478 // it). The node should be started if and only if this is
2479 // the first live input and there are no pending control
2480 // edges, i.e. count == 1.
2481 dst_ready = (count == 1);
2482 dst_need_input = ((count & 0x1) == 1);
2483 } else {
2484 // This is a dead data input. Note that dst_node is dead if node is
2485 // a dead enter. We need this to handle properly a while loop on
2486 // the untaken branch of a conditional.
2487 // TODO(yuanbyu): This is a bit hacky, but a good solution for
2488 // now.
2489 iter_state->increment_dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2490 const int dead_cnt = iter_state->dead_count(dst_pending_id);
2491 dst_dead = (dead_cnt == dst_item->num_inputs) || item->is_enter;
2492 dst_ready = (iter_state->pending(dst_pending_id) == 1) && dst_dead;
2493 dst_need_input = false;
2494 }
2495 }
2496 } else {
2497 const bool increment_dead =
2498 (is_dead || (!is_control_edge && !(*outputs)[src_slot].has_value));
2499 int pending, dead;
2500 iter_state->adjust_for_activation(dst_pending_id, increment_dead,
2501 &pending, &dead);
2502 dst_dead = (dead > 0);
2503 dst_ready = (pending == 0);
2504 }
2505
2506 if (dst_need_input) {
2507 const int dst_slot = e.input_slot;
2508 const int dst_loc = dst_item->input_start + dst_slot;
2509 if (e.is_last) {
2510 input_tensors[dst_loc] = std::move((*outputs)[src_slot]);
2511 } else {
2512 input_tensors[dst_loc] = (*outputs)[src_slot];
2513 }
2514 }
2515
2516 // Add dst to the ready queue if it's ready
2517 if (dst_ready) {
2518 if (dst_item->is_control_trigger) dst_dead = false;
2519 ready->push_back(TaggedNode(dst_item->node, this, iter, dst_dead));
2520 iter_state->outstanding_ops++;
2521 }
2522 }
2523}
2524
2525void ExecutorState::FrameState::ActivateNexts(const GraphView* gview,
2526 int64 iter,
2527 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2528 // Propagate the deferred NextIteration nodes to the new iteration.
2529 for (auto& node_entry : next_iter_roots) {
2530 const Node* node = node_entry.first;
2531 const Entry& entry = node_entry.second;
2532 const bool is_dead = !entry.has_value;
2533 const NodeItem* item = gview->node(node->id());
2534 EntryVector outputs{entry};
2535 ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, iter, &outputs, ready);
2536 }
2537 next_iter_roots.clear();
2538}
2539
2540void ExecutorState::FrameState::ActivateLoopInvs(const GraphView* gview,
2541 int64 iter,
2542 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2543 // Propagate loop invariants to the new iteration.
2544 for (auto& node_entry : inv_values) {
2545 const Node* node = node_entry.first;
2546 const Entry& entry = node_entry.second;
2547 const bool is_dead = !entry.has_value;
2548 const NodeItem* item = gview->node(node->id());
2549 EntryVector outputs{entry};
2550 ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, iter, &outputs, ready);
2551 }
2552}
2553
2554void ExecutorState::FrameState::AddLoopInv(const NodeItem* item,
2555 const Entry& entry,
2556 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2557 // Store this value.
2558 inv_values.push_back({item->node, entry});
2559
2560 // Make this value available to all iterations.
2561 const bool is_dead = !entry.has_value;
2562 for (int i = 0; i <= iteration_count; ++i) {
2563 EntryVector outputs{entry};
2564 ActivateNodes(item, is_dead, i, &outputs, ready);
2565 }
2566}
2567
2568bool ExecutorState::FrameState::IsIterationDone(int64 iter) {
2569 IterationState* iter_state = GetIteration(iter);
2570 if (iter_state->outstanding_ops == 0 &&
2571 iter_state->outstanding_frame_count == 0) {
2572 if (iter == 0) {
2573 // The enclosing frame has no pending input.
2574 return num_pending_inputs == 0;
2575 } else {
2576 // The preceding iteration is deleted (and therefore done).
2577 return (GetIteration(iter - 1) == nullptr);
2578 }
2579 }
2580 return false;
2581}
2582
2583void ExecutorState::FrameState::IncrementIteration(const GraphView* gview,
2584 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2585 iteration_count++;
2586 const int64 next_iter = iteration_count;
2587
2588 // Initialize the next iteration.
2589 IterationState* iter_state =
2590 new IterationState(pending_counts, total_input_tensors);
2591 SetIteration(next_iter, iter_state);
2592 num_outstanding_iterations++;
2593 dead_exits.clear();
2594
2595 // Activate the successors of the deferred roots in the new iteration.
2596 ActivateNexts(gview, next_iter, ready);
2597
2598 // Activate the loop invariants in the new iteration.
2599 ActivateLoopInvs(gview, next_iter, ready);
2600}
2601
2602bool ExecutorState::FrameState::CleanupIterations(const GraphView* gview,
2603 int64 iter,
2604 TaggedNodeSeq* ready) {
2605 int64 curr_iter = iter;
2606 while (curr_iter <= iteration_count && IsIterationDone(curr_iter)) {
2607 // Delete the iteration curr_iter.
2608 delete GetIteration(curr_iter);
2609 SetIteration(curr_iter, nullptr);
2610 --num_outstanding_iterations;
2611 ++curr_iter;
2612
2613 // When one iteration is completed, we check for deferred iteration,
2614 // and start it if there is one.
2615 if (!next_iter_roots.empty()) {
2616 IncrementIteration(gview, ready);
2617 }
2618 }
2619 return IsFrameDone();
2620}
2621
2622void ExecutorImpl::RunAsync(const Args& args, DoneCallback done) {
2623 (new ExecutorState(args, this))->RunAsync(std::move(done));
2624}

2628Status NewLocalExecutor(const LocalExecutorParams& params,
2629 std::unique_ptr<const Graph> graph,
2630 Executor** executor) {
2631 ExecutorImpl* impl = new ExecutorImpl(params, std::move(graph));
2632 const Status s = impl->Initialize();
2633 if (s.ok()) {
2634 *executor = impl;
2635 } else {
2636 delete impl;
2637 }
2638 return s;
2639}

2647 graph_def_version, kernel);
